{
  "doc_id": "17591",
  "text": "Mycobacterial panniculitis in cats caused by non-tuberculous mycobacterial species has been well described in the literature. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] One case report of M thermoresistibile pneumonia treatment exists in the literature. However, to the best of our knowledge, this is only the third report of mycobacterial panniculitis caused by M thermoresistibile in cats and the first report of attempted treatment of M thermoresistibile panniculitis. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The extent and severity of disease in this cat likely reflected a combination of delayed diagnosis and problems with owner compliance.",
